metadata.name: SETNAS #224
metadata.description:
SETNAS

-NOTES:

-100% code generated (no images or sounds preloaded)

-'Click' to START/pause.

-Save current frame to PNG-> press 'S' or  drag on top of screen.

-Save 2 s. animation to GIF-> press 'G' or drag on bottom of screen.

-All audio stuff is done with WebPd.

-All visual is done with p5js.

-Chrome browser recommended

-Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated.

-Supply can be halved/reduced and/or the price can be doubled if all iterations have not been minted (every 24h aprox).

DESCRIPTION:

-An audiovisual piece based on randomly generated patterns. These patterns generate endless unique pieces of electronic music (and their corresponding visuals).

-This is a 16-step sequencer based on 2 basic patterns: the kick drum and the tuplets of each kick.

-In each cycle (from 16 to 64 kicks) there can be changes to many of the parameters of the patterns, thus generating changes to the piece in an infinite way.

FEATURES:

-"tipusGrid": type of grid-> (lines, rects, soroll (noise), ASCII, mosaic or barcode).
-"baseShape": first cicle base shape (rect, circle,lines, vlines or hlines).
-"baseSize": size of base shape.
-"gridDensity": grid size (16, 32 or 64).
-"alpha": alpha of base image.
-"alpha2": alpha of canvas.
-"darkMode": dark mode (true) or light mode (false).
-"color": color of lines (dark mode) or background (light mode)-> white, red, green or blue.
-"bpm": Beats Per Minute. from 90 to 160 -> this value is theoretical, some devices may not be able to play the piece at a certain speed.
-"tipusBass": type of bass drum (from 0 to 5).
-"maxTuplet": max number of tuplets for each kick.
-"reverb": has reverb effect (audio)

metadata.name: September #101
metadata.description:
The Summer Ends
---------------
Controls:
S or double tap (mobile): Download image

A: Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)

1-6: Modify scale (1 = default, 1500 x 2000px, 6 = maximum, 9000 x 12000px (performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F: Fit to current screen size

T: Toggle grain and texture overlay
H: Toggle shape outlines

B: Cycle border sizes (0 -> 50 -> 75 -> 100 -> 150px)
C: Cycle border colors

I: Cycle visible layers

L: Toggle ‚Äúlive mode‚Äù. This mode will continuously redraw a new output every few seconds using the same base parameters as the original output, but with slight variations.

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------

metadata.name: BIP39_words v2 in 3D (2022year) #11
metadata.description:
Blockchain wallets are use BIP-39 to generate the mnemonic phrase. This NFT renders in 3D one random word from the BIP-39 english words list (it contains 2048 words).
You can click and rotate and type own word. Sometimes you are able to print own text. Sometimes NFT has geometric object.

Features:
- Word: one of 2048
- Background Color: one of 2 colors
- Font Color: ‚âà80 one of 4 colors or HSL in a range of 0 to 356 deg depend on hash.
- Editable: ‚âà24%
- Object Type: around 17% are has one of objects - 'sphere', 'box', 'dodecahedron', 'icosahedron' or ‚Äòoctahedron'

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #12
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: Blurevich #229
metadata.description:
"Blurevich"

The painting is characterized by its non-representational style, where the rectangles are not meant to depict recognizable objects or figures. 
Instead, the blurred rectangles serve as visual elements that create a sense of movement and dynamism in the painting. 
The use of blurriness in the rectangles gives the painting a hazy and ethereal quality. 
The colors used in the painting would  be bold and striking, creating a striking contrast between the sharp edges of the rectangles and the soft, blurred edges. 
The overall effect of the painting is one of abstraction and experimentation, express our emotions.
